headline: Oh Tannenbaum! Consumers Energy Helps Michigan Communities Plant Trees in the Right Place
summary: Consumers Energy is getting in the holiday spirit by celebrating the beauty and importance of trees. Through a partnership with the Michigan Forestry and Parks Association (MFPA), Consumers Energy has invested over $500,000 in tree planting grants since 2019, resulting in nearly 3,500 trees planted across its electric service territory, including 423 trees this year in 34 communities.
